# React & Kendo Patterns

## Client Components
- Use `"use client"` for components using hooks, Zustand, or browser APIs
- Server components for layouts, pages that only fetch/display data

## Navigation
```tsx
// Use i18n navigation (locale-aware)
import { Link, useRouter, usePathname } from "@/i18n/navigation";

router.push(`/${companyId}/master/port`);
<Link href="/login">Login</Link>
```

## Kendo Components
- Wrap app with `KendoIntlProvider` for locale (dates, numbers)
- Use `Controller` from react-hook-form with Kendo Input, Checkbox, etc.
- Grid: `MasterDataGrid` with `columns`, `actions`, `serverSidePagination` when needed

## Forms
- react-hook-form + zodResolver + zod schema
- Schemas in `schemas/`, interfaces in `interfaces/`

## Debug Logging
```tsx
import { debug } from "@/lib/debug";
debug.log("info");   // Only when NEXT_PUBLIC_DEBUG or dev
debug.error("err");  // Always logs
```
